00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:44,980
The common examples are the propositions of mathematics, geometry, algebra, formula logic.

135
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:51,180
Are all cases with the association where the truth of the sentences hinges on the relation

136
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:55,460
between the ideas and that relationship is purely formal.

137
00:10:55,460 --> 00:11:03,420
In other words, a computer can formulate true mathematical or logical propositions.

138
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:10,740
The key for Hume is that such propositions have absolutely no existential implications.

139
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:14,540
We can accept all of Euclidean geometry as being true.

140
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:18,580
Every proposition, provable in the Euclidean geometry, we can accept is true without there

