00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:26,380
Similarly, we can accept all the propositions as logic as true without believing that there

143
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:33,060
exists somewhere in the world a operator called the conditional or the disjunctive.

144
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:39,140
So that's a key point that that first class of knowledge, the relation between ideas is

145
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:42,060
purely formal and has no existential implications.

146
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:46,300
It teaches us nothing about the world, it only teaches us, as it were, a very rigorous

147
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:50,780
sort of vocabulary that we might be able to use in talking about the world.

148
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:57,100
In and of itself has nothing to say about existence and things of the world.

149
00:11:57,100 --> 00:12:04,660
Things of the world are discussed in that second class of knowledge, which he calls

150
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:07,180
matters of fact.

