00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:20,100
It's the fundamental glue, as it were, epistemological glue of the factual world, because it allows

183
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:24,620
us to infer from sense to uncensed phenomena.

184
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:30,260
Now cause and effect is not known what we might call a priori, or before the fact, or

185
00:14:30,260 --> 00:14:32,140
before experience.

186
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:37,740
Rather, it only comes from the experience of constant conjunction.

187
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:40,700
So again, back to our great experiment.

188
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:45,340
You did not know before you ever saw someone release an object that it would fall.

189
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:51,580
The only way you know that is that every time you've seen an object released, it falls.

190
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:58,980
That constant conjunction, release, fall, release, fall, is the only evidence you have

191
00:14:58,980 --> 00:15:04,220
of that causal relation, and similarly it is with all the other causal relations.

192
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:08,540
The only way you know that eating a cheeseburger will satisfy you when you're hungry, if in

193
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:12,740
fact it does, is because that's happened in the past.

